Methods
We used data from the Brazilian National Survey (PNS 2019), a population-based study, with complex and probabilistic sampling method. There were 94,114 participants with complete information about the use of TCIM. All participants answered a questionnaire containing sociodemographic, clinical data and information about their TCIM use during the last 12 months. The Patient Health Questionnaire-9 (PHQ-9) was used to assess depression. All variables were categorized. Logistic regression models were performed to obtain crude and adjusted odds ratios (OR) and 95% confidence intervals (95%CI).
